{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Sh2GXL7Gnk4yQ7tbS2NEbc","type":"tool_result","content":"<system-reminder>This memory is 3 days old. Memories are point-in-time observations, not live state — claims about code behavior or file:line citations may be outdated. Verify against current code before asserting as fact.</system-reminder>\n     1→---\n     2→name: STEP 02 Template Constraints\n     3→description: Template instruction constraints from each worksheet of the Vendor Spend Strategy workbook; governs formatting and output rules for later steps\n     4→type: project\n     5→---\n     6→\n     7→Template workbook: outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx\n     8→\n     9→## Sheet A1 Instructions\n    10→\n    11→- **Vendor Analysis Assessment**: Header row only (`Vendor Name`) — no special constraints\n    12→- **Top 3 Opportunities**: Empty — structure governed by column headers\n    13→- **Methodology**: Must explain approach, prompt(s), and tools used\n    14→- **CEOCFO Recommendations**: Short memo, **maximum 1 page**; audience is CEO/CFO; concise and high-signal; must include a Google Doc link in the cell\n    15→- **Config**: Header row only (`Department`) — no special constraints\n    16→- **First Quick Analysis**: Empty — no embedded constraints\n    17→\n    18→## Binding Constraints\n    19→\n    20→1. CEO/CFO memo hard cap: **1 page maximum**\n    21→2. CEO/CFO audience: busy senior executives — no over-explaining, focus on what matters\n    22→3. CEO/CFO delivery: Google Doc link required in the sheet cell\n    23→4. Methodology sheet: reflective write-up of process, tools, and prompts used\n    24→\n    25→**Why:** These constraints are embedded directly in the template by the assessment author and override workflow guidance where they conflict.\n    26→**How to apply:** Check these constraints before drafting STEP 09 (CEO/CFO memo) and STEP 10 (Methodology write-up).\n    27→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"22ec7121-f94a-4f75-a15f-c898f36a41cd","uuid":"a9586465-a054-42a0-a635-99b3635ebf40","timestamp":"2026-03-20T20:18:07.112Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:/Users/rjega/.claude/projects/C--Users-rjega-vendor-spend-analysis/memory/project_step02_template_constraints.md","content":"---\nname: STEP 02 Template Constraints\ndescription: Template instruction constraints from each worksheet of the Vendor Spend Strategy workbook; governs formatting and output rules for later steps\ntype: project\n---\n\nTemplate workbook: outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx\n\n## Sheet A1 Instructions\n\n- **Vendor Analysis Assessment**: Header row only (`Vendor Name`) — no special constraints\n- **Top 3 Opportunities**: Empty — structure governed by column headers\n- **Methodology**: Must explain approach, prompt(s), and tools used\n- **CEOCFO Recommendations**: Short memo, **maximum 1 page**; audience is CEO/CFO; concise and high-signal; must include a Google Doc link in the cell\n- **Config**: Header row only (`Department`) — no special constraints\n- **First Quick Analysis**: Empty — no embedded constraints\n\n## Binding Constraints\n\n1. CEO/CFO memo hard cap: **1 page maximum**\n2. CEO/CFO audience: busy senior executives — no over-explaining, focus on what matters\n3. CEO/CFO delivery: Google Doc link required in the sheet cell\n4. Methodology sheet: reflective write-up of process, tools, and prompts used\n\n**Why:** These constraints are embedded directly in the template by the assessment author and override workflow guidance where they conflict.\n**How to apply:** Check these constraints before drafting STEP 09 (CEO/CFO memo) and STEP 10 (Methodology write-up).\n","numLines":27,"startLine":1,"totalLines":27}}}
